ts register 150\u00b0F on an instant read thermometer, about 15 minutes. Transfer chicken breasts to a bowl and let rest. Continue simmering broth and beans until beans are fully tender, about 30 minutes. Remove 1 1/2 cups of beans and their liquid and transfer to a standing blender or the work cup of an immersion blender. Blend until completely smooth. Stir back into pot. Heat a cast iron skillet over high heat. Add 1 can drained corn to the skillet with 1 tbsp oil. Blacken the corn, turning a few times while cooking. Cook about 5 minutes. Shred chicken into bite-sized pieces and stir back into stew. Stir in jalape\u00f1o pickling liquid, lime juice, and half of cilantro. Season to taste with salt.",
